location: The incident occurred in the al-Tshash area near the city.
summary: 07/29/2013: Assailants shot and killed two police officers in Al-Tshash area, Kut city, Wasit governorate, Iraq. This was one of 24 coordinated attacks in Iraq on the same day. Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant (ISIL) claimed responsibility, stating that the coordinated incidents were part of campaign called "warrior harvest."
